translated: Kindblom, Nils Olof, chief veterinarian, Jönköping, b. June 20, 1909 in Bysike, Västerbotten County. Married at the county hospital. Spouse's name: Holst. They had a son named Per Olof born in 1933. Nils Olof graduated from Lund's private school in 1928 and obtained his veterinary degree in 1940. He worked as an assistant at the state veterinary laboratory from 1939 to 1945 and became the chief veterinarian in Jönköping in 1945.
